        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-21T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-21T19:00:00-05:00" n="694" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d694">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/8–2145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-21T20:00:00-04:00">August 21, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1880. With reference to your telegrams concerning the Stalin–Soong discussions, I
                    would appreciate receiving whatever information you may have with regard to the
                    progress that was made in the discussion relative to assurances which the Soviet
                    and Chinese Governments agreed to give us that the Open Door policy will be
                    respected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
